bug.short_desc: multiple instances of file-roller are not usable, also 10 seconds after starting+quitting file-roller
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1201168 bug demonstration video
Description of problem: This is a regression between file-roller-3.21.90-1.fc25.x86_64 and file-roller-3.21.91-1.fc25.x86_64.
You can't have two file-roller windows opened at once. The first one shows content OK, but the second one (or any later one) shows just a gray uninitialized window with not content displayed.
This also happens for just a single window, if you start the second window sooner than 10 seconds after starting the first one. So for example you can't do this: 1. display archive contents in file-roller 2. immediately quit it 3. show the same archive (or a different one) again -- if there was less than 10 seconds since step 1, the window will be gray and empty
See the video.
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): file-roller-3.21.91-1.fc25.x86_64
How reproducible: always
Steps to Reproduce: 1. open an archive with file-roller 2. quit it 3. again open an archive with file-roller (in 10 seconds since step 1), the window will be empty -or- 1. open an archive with file-roller, keep it open 2. open a different archive with file-roller, the window will be empty
*** Bug 1376388 has been marked as a duplicate of this bug. ***
This happens in X11 session and Wayland session all the same.

(In reply to Kalev Lember from comment #3) > Should be fixed in file-roller-3.21.91-2.fc25
Great, that fixes this problem.
